Hurtigruten Involved in 29 Accidents in Past Five Years, DN Says

-- B y   S t e p h e n   T r e l o a r
-- 
2011-09-16T06:40:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/hurtigruten-involved-in-29-accidents-in-past-five-years-dn-says.html
Hurtigruten ASA (HRG)  was involved in 29
accidents in the past five years prior to yesterday’s deadly
fire on a cruise ship, Dagens Naeringsliv reported, citing
documents it obtained from the Norwegian Maritime Directorate.  There were 12 instances of Hurtigruten-operated ships
running aground and a fire before yesterday’s incident on the
western coast of  Norway , the Oslo-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Treloar at 
